import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    bin_index = np.arange(len(bins))
    rest_capacity = bins - item

import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    bin_indices = np.where(bins > item)[0]
    scores = np.zeros_like(bins)
    if len(bin_indices) == 0:
        return scores
    
    bin_sizes = bins[bin_indices]
    ratios = (bin_indices * (1/item)) / bin_sizes
    scores[bin_indices] = ratios - np.square(item)
    return scores

def score(item, bins):

import numpy as np

def score(item, bins):
    beta = 0.5  # Adjust the importance of rest capacity in scoring
    delta = 0.1  # Adjust the influence of bin index in scoring

    indices = np.arange(len(bins))
    rest_capacity = bins - item

    scores = (beta / rest_capacity) / (indices - delta)
    scores[rest_capacity == bins] = -np.inf

    return scores
